In the last article, I introduced the try-catch IIFE pattern. Some of you found it clever, while others couldn‚Äôt stand the syntax. And honestly? Fair. IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression) can look odd at first glance.
But I‚Äôm here to change your mind.
IIFE isn‚Äôt just a relic of the var era, there are still many modern use cases.
Here are 7 modern use cases of IIFE that go beyond legacy code and show how they can improve clarity, encapsulation, and expressiveness in your everyday code.
